text: The WAGR Ta class were a total of 10 diesel-electric shunting locomotives operated by the Western Australian Government Railways (WAGR) from 1968/9 to 1994. The Ta class were a more powerful version of the standard T class shunters, they were one of the last locomotives to be constructed by Tulloch Limited of Rhodes, Sydney, New South Wales. The last of the class was withdrawn in 1994, with the exception of No. 1807 which works for the State Energy Commission at Bunbury (as of 2010). 3 examples have been scrapped, with 6 scrapped.
